Description: Fix 64-bit portability issues
 - model.h: T3D_Color and T3D_Vector fields double -> float
   (coordinates are used exclusively with glVertex2f/glColor4f which
   expect GLfloat; passing double caused implicit narrowing on every call)
 - model.c: sscanf format %lf -> %f to match float fields
 - model.c: glColor4f literal constants suffixed with f (1.1 -> 1.1f etc.)
   to avoid -Wdouble-promotion with GCC 15
 - model.c: density(): abs() on float -> fabsf() (<math.h> already included);
   abs() silently truncated the float to int before computing absolute value
 - model.c: density(): remove unused variable 'step' (-Wunused-variable)
 - main.c: integer division of Uint32 before implicit float conversion
   replaced with explicit float arithmetic (now - 46000) / 100 -> (float)(now - 46000) / 100.0f
